Bash("c:/Users/seanb/miniconda3/python.exe" -c "
import json, os
os.system\(''cls''\)

# Export for each config
configs = [
    ''configs/fish_overhead.json'',
    ''configs/longboard_small.json'',
]

for configPath in configs:
    # Temporarily set the configPath and run the pipeline
    with open\(configPath, ''r''\) as f:
        config = json.load\(f\)

    print\(f''\\nProcessing: {configPath}''\)

    from SurfPhysics.analyzer import PhysicsAnalyzer
    from SurfPhysics.export.viewerExporter import ViewerExporter

    analyzer = PhysicsAnalyzer\(\)
    analyzer.runAnalysis\(configPath\)

    viewerConfig = config.get\(''viewer'', {}\)
    if viewerConfig.get\(''export'', False\):
        exporter = ViewerExporter\(\)
        stlDir = config.get\(''geometry'', {}\).get\(''outputDir'', ''SurfboardGeometry/Output''\)
        outputDir = viewerConfig.get\(''outputDir'', ''SurfViewer/data''\)
        exporter.exportForViewer\(
            analyzer.results,
            stlDir=stlDir,
            outputDir=outputDir,
        \)
")

from SurfPhysics.geometry.parameters import SurfboardParameters
from SurfPhysics.geometry.surfaceMeshGenerator import SurfaceMeshGenerator

# Test all three presets
for name, factory in [\(''shortboard'', SurfboardParameters.shortboard\),
                       \(''longboard'', SurfboardParameters.longboard\),
                       \(''fish'', SurfboardParameters.fish\)]:
    params = factory\(\)
    gen = SurfaceMeshGenerator.fromPreset\(params, ''standard''\)
    mesh = gen.generate\(\)
    print\(f''{name}: verts={len\(mesh.vertices\)}, faces={len\(mesh.faces\)}, ''
          f''watertight={mesh.is_watertight}, vol={gen.computeVolumeLiters\(\):.2f}L''\)

# Export a shortboard STL for visual inspection
params = SurfboardParameters.shortboard\(\)
gen = SurfaceMeshGenerator.fromPreset\(params, ''standard''\)
gen.exportStl\(''SurfboardGeometry/Output/shortboard_parametric.stl''\)
print\(''Exported shortboard_parametric.stl''\)

# Also test draft and high resolution
for preset in [''draft'', ''high'']:
    gen = SurfaceMeshGenerator.fromPreset\(params, preset\)
    mesh = gen.generate\(\)
    print\(f''{preset}: verts={len\(mesh.vertices\)}, faces={len\(mesh.faces\)}, ''
          f''watertight={mesh.is_watertight}, vol={gen.computeVolumeLiters\(\):.2f}L''\)
")

Bash("C:/Users/seanb/miniconda3/python.exe" -c "
from SurfPhysics.validation.reverseEngineer import ReverseEngineer

# Load the reference thruster
re = ReverseEngineer\(
    ''SurfPhysics/validation/meshes/referenceThruster.stl'',
    expectedLengthMm=1828.0,
\)
print\(f''Board length: {re.boardLengthMm:.1f} mm''\)

# Extract profiles
profiles = re.extractProfiles\(nStations=200, nLateralSamples=50\)
print\(f''Max width: {profiles.maxWidthMm:.1f} mm''\)
print\(f''Max thickness: {profiles.maxThicknessMm:.1f} mm''\)
print\(f''Nose rocker: {profiles.rockerHeights[0]:.1f} mm''\)
print\(f''Tail rocker: {profiles.rockerHeights[-1]:.1f} mm''\)

# Fit parameters
params = re.fitParameters\(profiles\)
params.printSummary\(\)

# Compare fitted params against the extracted profiles
comparison = re.compareToParametric\(params, profiles\)
print\(\)
print\(''Comparison \(fitted params vs. extracted profiles\):''\)
for key, val in comparison.items\(\):
    print\(f''  {key}: {val}''\)
")

Bash("C:/Users/seanb/miniconda3/python.exe" -c "
from SurfPhysics.geometry.parameters import SurfboardParameters
from SurfPhysics.validation.reverseEngineer import ReverseEngineer

params = SurfboardParameters.shortboard\(\)

# Reverse-engineer the parametric STL we already generated
re = ReverseEngineer\(
    ''SurfboardGeometry/Output/shortboard_parametric.stl'',
    expectedLengthMm=1828.0,
    removeFins=False,
    autoTransform=False,
\)

profiles = re.extractProfiles\(nStations=200, nLateralSamples=50\)
fittedParams = re.fitParameters\(profiles\)

print\(''-- Fitted vs. Original --''\)
fields = [
    \(''Length'', ''length''\), \(''Max Width'', ''maxWidth''\), \(''Max Thick'', ''maxThickness''\),
    \(''Nose Width'', ''noseWidth''\), \(''Tail Width'', ''tailWidth''\),
    \(''WP Offset'', ''widePointOffset''\), \(''Tail Tip HW'', ''tailTipHalfWidth''\),
    \(''Nose Rocker'', ''noseRocker''\), \(''Tail Rocker'', ''tailRocker''\),
    \(''Deck Crown'', ''deckCrown''\), \(''Concave'', ''bottomConcave''\),
]
for label, attr in fields:
    fitted = getattr\(fittedParams, attr\)
    original = getattr\(params, attr\)
    diff = abs\(fitted - original\)
    mark = ''OK'' if diff < 3.0 else ''MISS''
    print\(f''  {label:14s}: {fitted:8.1f}  vs {original:8.1f}  \(diff: {diff:5.1f}\) {mark}''\)

comparison = re.compareToParametric\(fittedParams, profiles\)
print\(\)
print\(''Round-trip RMS errors:''\)
for key, val in comparison.items\(\):
    print\(f''  {key}: {val}''\)
")

import numpy as np
from SurfPhysics.geometry.parameters import SurfboardParameters
from SurfPhysics.validation.reverseEngineer import ReverseEngineer
from SurfPhysics.geometry.outline import Outline

params = SurfboardParameters.shortboard\(\)
outline = Outline\(params\)

re = ReverseEngineer\(
    ''SurfboardGeometry/Output/shortboard_parametric.stl'',
    expectedLengthMm=1828.0, removeFins=False, autoTransform=False,
\)
profiles = re.extractProfiles\(nStations=200, nLateralSamples=50\)

# Compare extracted vs parametric half-widths near the tail
print\(''Tail region comparison \(last 10 stations\):''\)
print\(f''{""t"":>8s}  {""extracted"":>10s}  {""parametric"":>10s}  {""diff"":>8s}''\)
for i in range\(-10, 0\):
    t = float\(profiles.tValues[i]\)
    extHw = float\(profiles.halfWidths[i]\)
    paramHw = outline.getHalfWidth\(t\)
    print\(f''{t:8.4f}  {extHw:10.2f}  {paramHw:10.2f}  {extHw-paramHw:8.2f}''\)

# Also check the very last few values
print\(\)
print\(f''Last extracted t: {profiles.tValues[-1]:.6f}''\)
print\(f''Last extracted halfWidth: {profiles.halfWidths[-1]:.2f}''\)
print\(f''Parametric at that t: {outline.getHalfWidth\(float\(profiles.tValues[-1]\)\):.2f}''\)
print\(f''Parametric at t=1.0: {outline.getHalfWidth\(1.0\):.2f}''\)
")

Bash("C:/Users/seanb/miniconda3/python.exe" -c "
from SurfPhysics.geometry.parameters import SurfboardParameters
from SurfPhysics.validation.reverseEngineer import ReverseEngineer

# Full round-trip: reverse-engineer each preset''s generated STL
presets = {
    ''shortboard'': SurfboardParameters.shortboard\(\),
    ''longboard'': SurfboardParameters.longboard\(\),
    ''fish'': SurfboardParameters.fish\(\),
}

for name, originalParams in presets.items\(\):
    print\(f''=== {name.upper\(\)} ===''\)
    re = ReverseEngineer\(
        f''SurfboardGeometry/Output/{name}_parametric.stl'',
        expectedLengthMm=originalParams.length,
        removeFins=False,
        autoTransform=False,
    \)
    profiles = re.extractProfiles\(nStations=200\)
    fittedParams = re.fitParameters\(profiles\)
    comparison = re.compareToParametric\(fittedParams, profiles\)

    print\(f''  Volume:    {fittedParams.approxVolumeLiters:.1f}L''\)
    print\(f''  Length:    {fittedParams.length:.0f} vs {originalParams.length:.0f}''\)
    print\(f''  Width:     {fittedParams.maxWidth:.1f} vs {originalParams.maxWidth:.1f}''\)
    print\(f''  Thickness: {fittedParams.maxThickness:.1f} vs {originalParams.maxThickness:.1f}''\)
    print\(f''  Outline RMS: {comparison[""outlineRmsMm""]:.2f} mm''\)
    print\(f''  Rocker RMS:  {comparison[""rockerRmsMm""]:.2f} mm''\)
    print\(f''  Thick RMS:   {comparison[""thicknessRmsMm""]:.2f} mm''\)
    print\(\)
")
